{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"WebSocket.close()","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSocket/close","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSocket\"><code>WebSocket</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Constructor</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSocket/WebSocket\"><code>WebSocket()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSocket/binaryType\"><code>binaryType</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSocket/bufferedAmount\"><code>bufferedAmount</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSocket/extensions\"><code>extensions</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSocket/protocol\"><code>protocol</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSocket/readyState\"><code>readyState</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSocket/url\"><code>url</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Methods</summary><ol><li><em><code>close()</code></em></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSocket/send\"><code>send()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Events</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSocket/close_event\"><code>close</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSocket/error_event\"><code>error</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSocket/message_event\"><code>message</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSocket/open_event\"><code>open</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance:</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget\"><code>EventTarget</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The <strong><code>WebSocket.close()</code></strong> method closes the\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSocket\"><code>WebSocket</code></a> connection or connection attempt, if any. If the connection is\n  already <code>CLOSED</code>, this method does nothing.\n</p>\n<div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect1\">\n  <p><strong>Note:</strong> The process of closing the connection begins with a <a href=\"https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc6455.html#section-1.4\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">closing handshake</a>, and the <code>close()</code> method does not discard previously-sent messages before starting that closing handshake; even if the user agent is still busy sending those messages, the handshake will only start after the messages are sent.</p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js-nolint notranslate\">close()\nclose(code)\nclose(code, reason)\n</pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"code\"><code>code</code> <span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>An integer <a href=\"https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc6455.html#section-7.1.5\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">WebSocket connection close code</a> value indicating a reason for closure:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>If unspecified, a close code for the connection is automatically set: to <code>1000</code> for a normal closure, or otherwise to <a href=\"https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc6455.html#section-7.4.1\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">another standard value in the range <code>1001</code>-<code>1015</code></a> that indicates the actual reason the connection was closed.</li>\n      <li>\n        If specified, the value of this <code>code</code> parameter overrides the automatic setting of the close code for the connection, and instead sets a custom code.\n        The value must be an integer: either <code>1000</code>, or else a custom code of your choosing in the range <code>3000</code>-<code>4999</code>. If you specify a <code>code</code> value, you should also specify a <a href=\"#reason\"><code>reason</code></a> value.\n      </li>\n    </ul>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"reason\"><code>reason</code> <span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>A string providing a custom <a href=\"https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc6455.html#section-7.1.6\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">WebSocket connection close reason</a> (a concise human-readable prose explanation for the closure). The value must be no longer than 123 bytes (encoded in UTF-8).</p>\n    <div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect2\">\n      <p><strong>Note:</strong> Because <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Glossary/UTF-8\">UTF-8 uses two to four bytes</a> to encode any non-<a href=\"/en-US/docs/Glossary/ASCII\">ASCII</a> characters, a 123-character <code>reason</code> value containing non-ASCII characters would exceed the 123-byte limit.</p>\n    </div>\n    <p>If you specify a <code>reason</code> value, you should also specify a <a href=\"#code\"><code>code</code></a> value.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return value","isH3":true,"content":"<p>None (<a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/undefined\"><code>undefined</code></a>).</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"exceptions","title":"Exceptions","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"invalidaccesserror\"><code>InvalidAccessError</code> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMException\"><code>DOMException</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Thrown if <a href=\"#code\"><code>code</code></a> is neither an integer equal to <code>1000</code> nor an integer in the range <code>3000</code>–<code>4999</code>.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"syntaxerror\"><code>SyntaxError</code> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMException\"><code>DOMException</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Thrown if the UTF-8-encoded <a href=\"#reason\"><code>reason</code></a> value is longer than 123 bytes.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/web-sockets.html#dom-websocket-close-dev","title":"HTML Standard"}],"query":"api.WebSocket.close"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.WebSocket.close","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSocket/close/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc6455.html\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">RFC 6455</a> (the WebSocket Protocol specification)</li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The WebSocket.close() method closes the\n  WebSocket connection or connection attempt, if any. If the connection is\n  already CLOSED, this method does nothing.","popularity":0.0033,"modified":"2022-09-13T06:51:25.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"WebSocket.close()","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"WebSocket.close()","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"WebSocket.close()","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/websocket/close","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/websocket/close/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/c575deb5f1775b532360c612a85b35a5ff9525d9","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSocket","title":"WebSocket"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSocket/close","title":"WebSocket.close()"}],"pageTitle":"WebSocket.close() - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}